[normal]Written evidence submitted by Hhic And Hwa (HOT12) [bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Introduction[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The Heating and Hotwater Industry Council (HHIC) and the Hot
[normal] W
[normal]ater Association (HWA) welcome the opportunity to respond to the Energy
[normal] and Cli
[normal]mate Change Select Committee’s Inquiry into H
[normal]eat.  HHIC and HWA 
[normal]are trade associations 
[normal]work
[normal]ing
[normal] together under the umbrella of t
[normal]he Energy &amp; Utilities Alliance to provide 
[normal]widespread
[normal] representation of the domestic heating 
[normal]and hot water 
[normal]industry
[normal] which 
[normal]is worth 
[normal]£3-4 billion
[normal].  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]HHIC members include manufacturers, merchants and installers of all types of heating products including traditional fossil fuel boilers, microCHP
[normal], heat pumps, biomass boilers and solar water heaters. HWA represents manufacturers of hot water storage products. 
[normal]93-95% of heating and hot water solutions in the UK are covered by HHIC’s and HWA’s membership.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We would be happy to discuss any of the issu
[normal]es rais
[normal]ed in this response and in the I
[normal]nquiry with the Select Committee. 
